OL,3,CElectric car owners unhappy with
OL,4,Ccharging infrastructure ` survey
OL,6,FWhich? head of consumer protection
OL,7,Fpolicy Sue Davies said: "We know that
OL,8,Fpeople want to make more sustainable
OL,9,Fchoices and switch to an electric
OL,10,Fvehicle, but many drivers have a lack
OL,11,Fof confidence in the public charging
OL,12,Finfrastructure, and this also risks
OL,13,Falienating people who aren't able to
OL,14,Fcharge their EVs at home.
OL,16,F"It is positive that the Government
OL,17,Fpassed new rules that should see
OL,18,Fimprovements in consumers' experiences
OL,19,Fof the public charging network.
